es of India"},{"id":"483495","title":"UCO Bank revises TBLR and G-Sec linked rates effective 11.02.2026.\nMCLR, Repo Linked Rate, Base Rate, and BPLR remain unchanged.","summary":"UCO Bank revises TBLR and G-Sec linked rates effective 11.02.2026.\nMCLR, Repo Linked Rate, Base Rate, and BPLR remain unchanged.","url":"https://www.bseindia.com/stockinfo/AnnPdfOpen.aspx?Pname=808ec647-10c1-4ed1-832d-b672b77252e0.pdf","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-10T17:51:53","source":"BSE"},{"id":"804281731886094720","title":"UCO Bank's business grew 13.3% YoY, driven by 10.6% deposit and 16.7% advances growth.\nNet profit rose 15.7%, NIM improved to 3.1%, and Gross NPA reduced to 2.4%.","summary":"UCO Bank's business grew 13.3% YoY, driven by 10.6% deposit and 16.7% advances growth.\nNet profit rose 15.7%, NIM improved to 3.1%, and Gross NPA reduced to 2.4%.","url":"https://sqst.in/Ibeto","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-28T14:58:27","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"260128141741357","title":"PSU banks like Punjab & Sind Bank, UCO Bank, Bank of Maharashtra, IOB, and Central Bank of India reported strong Q3FY26 results, driven by profit growth and rising net interest income.\nKey highlights: IOB's net profit surged 56%, Bank of Maharashtra's by 27%, and Central Bank of India's by 31%, boosting investor sentiment.","summary":"PSU banks like Punjab & Sind Bank, UCO Bank, Bank of Maharashtra, IOB, and Central Bank of India reported strong Q3FY26 results, driven by profit growth and rising net interest income.\nKey highlights: IOB's net profit surged 56%, Bank of Maharashtra's by 27%, and Central Bank of India's by 31%, boosting investor sentiment.","url":"https://tradebrains.in/psu-bank-stocks-that-delivered-net-profit-growth-of-up-to-56-in-q3-to-look-out-for/","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-28T14:00:00","source":"Trade Brains"},{"id":"453417","title":"UCO Bank reports a potential strike by UFBU on 27th Jan 2026.\nBank ensures measures for smooth operations but warns of possible di